### 🛡️ Heimdall Quality: Test Engineering Profile

Below is the formal YAML configuration for the Heimdall Quality static analysis engine, codifying these concepts into an automated gatekeeper.

```yaml
profile: "Heimdall-Test-Optima"
description: "Optimized for DAMP principles, test isolation, and deterministic execution."

scope:
  discovery:
    path_patterns: ["**/tests/**", "**/__tests__/**", "**/*.spec.*", "**/*_test.*"]
    ast_signatures: ["@Test", "@ParameterizedTest", "it(", "describe("]

rules:
  # 1. THE COMPLEXITY PARADOX
  complexity:
    cyclomatic:
      threshold: 25 # (Prod default: 10) - Accommodates heavy assertions/data tables
      severity: "INFO"
    cognitive:
      threshold: 2  # (Prod default: 15) - Tests must be flat AAA logic
      severity: "CRITICAL"
      failure_message: "Test logic contains branching (if/else) or loops. Tests must be deterministic."
    setup_friction:
      max_arrange_lines: 15
      severity: "WARNING"
      failure_message: "Setup is too complex. Refactor the production API to reduce coupling/constructor friction."

  # 2. DUPLICATION (DAMP over DRY)
  duplication:
    clone_detection:
      min_lines: 18       # (Prod default: 6) - Allows copy-pasting of AAA setups
      min_tokens: 150     # (Prod default: 50)
      severity: "WARNING"
      ignore_ast_nodes: 
        - "ImportDeclaration"
        - "ObjectExpression" # Ignore duplicated JSON mock payloads

  # 3. DOCUMENTATION 
  documentation:
    test_functions:
      require_docstring: false
      enforce_naming_convention: 
        regex: "^(test|it|should)_[a-z0-9_]+"
        min_length: 15 # Forces descriptive sentences (e.g. test_user_is_locked_out)
        severity: "WARNING"
    test_infrastructure: # Fixtures, factories, helpers
      require_docstring: true
      require_type_hints: true
      severity: "ERROR"

  # 4. TEST-EXCLUSIVE METRICS
  test_health:
    assertion_density:
      min_per_test: 1
      max_per_test: 10
      ignore_parameterized: true
      failure_message: "Test is an 'Eager Test' verifying too much. Split into smaller units."
    
    test_to_prod_ratio:
      warning_low: 0.5   # Undertested
      warning_high: 4.0  # Over-mocked / Brittle
      
    hermeticity:
      block_unmocked_io: true
      forbidden_calls: ["sleep", "setTimeout", "Thread.sleep"]
      forbidden_imports: ["http", "socket", "urllib", "fs"]
      failure_message: "Hermeticity violation. Unit tests must not perform real I/O or arbitrary sleeps."
      
    coupling:
      detect_shared_mutable_state: true
      allow_unrestored_global_mutation: false
      failure_message: "Global state mutated without teardown. High risk of test pollution/flakiness."

```